Cameroon has completed the
construction of two pipes into lake Nyos to prevent a repeat of
the build-up of carbon dioxide in 1986 that suffocated more than
1,700 people.  The pipes were built by the French company DATA
Environnement, Joseph Victor Hell, the director of the countryâ€™s
Institute of Geological and Mineral Research, said at the lake
